.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.LP
When called, '\fB²DPROG²\fR' accomplishes the following:
.LP
\fB1)\fR General and program-specific defaults are set.
.LP
\fB2)\fR Defaults are loaded from the configuration file, if it exists (default: \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory as \fB²DPROG²\fR, default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/²DPROG²\fR).
.LP
\fB3)\fR Command line arguments are evaluated and override the configuration file where applicable.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Questions are asked if values are missing or an interactive option is set.
.LP
\fB5)\fR The required directories (source, archive, target and second target) are checked and created if needed; their inclusion in the samba server is verified.
.LP
\fB6)\fR The program inserts itself if wanted and necessary into root's \fBcrontab\fR in order to be called in adjustable intervals.
.LP
\fB7)\fR The availability of \fBdcmtk\fR (in particular \fBdcmdump\fR and \fBdcmj2pnm\fR) is checked; if missing or too old (< 3.62), \fBdcmtk\fR is installed or compiled from source.
.LP
\fB8)\fR The MariaDB database is initialised and the table \fBdictab\fR (or the configured table name) is checked and if necessary created or amended. The table contains the following fields: \fBID\fR, \fBPatientName\fR, \fBGeburtsdatum\fR, \fBPatientID\fR, \fBGeschlecht\fR, \fBBildtyp\fR, \fBReferringPhysicianName\fR, \fBPerformingPhysicianName\fR, \fBTransducerData\fR, \fBProcessingFunction\fR, \fBMediaStorageSOPInstanceUID\fR, \fBAufnahmedatum\fR, \fBImportdatum\fR.
.LP
\fB9)\fR If the option \fB-back\fR is set, the last import is reverted and the program exits.
.LP
\fB10)\fR An import subdirectory is created under the archive directory, named after the current timestamp (e.g. \fB20240315_143012\fR).
.LP
\fB11)\fR All eligible files in the source directory (or, with \fB-ra\fR, the archive directory) are located via \fBfind\fR: files without extension as well as files with extension \fB.dcm\fR or \fB.DCM\fR, newer than 2017-01-01, not containing 'DICOMDIR' in their path. Any pure \fB.DCM\fR suffixes are removed beforehand via \fBrename\fR.
.LP
\fB12)\fR For each found file, the DICOM header is read with \fBdcmdump\fR and the metadata is written to the database table. If the file (identified by \fBMediaStorageSOPInstanceUID\fR, \fBPatientName\fR, birth date, \fBPatientID\fR and acquisition date) is already present, it is skipped — unless \fB-nm\fR (redo) is set.
.LP
\fB13)\fR New records (or all records if \fB-nm\fR is set) are converted to PNG files with \fBdcmj2pnm\fR and placed in the target directory. The PNG filename is composed of the metadata. Afterwards the image is also copied to the second target directory in a year-based subdirectory. File ownership and timestamp are set to the acquisition time.
.LP
\fB14)\fR If no error occurred (and \fB-ra\fR is not set), all processed source files are moved into the timestamped subdirectory under the archive directory.
.LP
\fB15)\fR The configuration file is written if necessary.
.LP
\fB16)\fR A summary displays the number of DICOM files found, records inserted, PNG images created and files copied or moved.
.SH PRECONDITIONS
\fBHardware\fR: Computer with network or filesystem access to the source directory (e.g. an ultrasound device writing DICOM files to a network share).
.br
\fBSoftware\fR: The program is adjusted to an installation of Opensuse >= 42.1, Debian >= 9, Ubuntu >= 16.04, Mint >= 18 or Fedora >= 24 with standard options. System D must be installed. One of the packet managers \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR or \fBzypper\fR must be installed. The program '\fBwget\fR' must be installed. MariaDB must be running.
.SH AUTOMATICALLY INSTALLED SOFTWARE PACKAGES
.br
(for this purpose, depending on the distribution, zypper, apt(-get), dnf or yum are used).
.LP
\fI\fBmakefile:\fR
.br
gcc V.6 or higher, g++ V.6 or higher, groff, libmysqlclient-dev(el), libtiff-dev(el)
.LP
\fI\fB²DPROG²:\fR
.br
acl, boost, boost-devel, boost-locale, cron, dcmtk (>= 3.62, compiled from source if necessary), libtiff, mariadb-server, samba
.SH IMPLICATIONS
The program has to take the following measures for its neat function:
.LP
\fB1)\fR Sudo (is missing per default in debian) will be installed if needed.
.br
The current linux user, if not already contained, will be entered into an administrator group mentioned in /etc/sudoers.
.LP
\fB2)\fR 'GNU make' will be installed if not present, automatically by calling 'sh install.sh'.
.LP
\fB3)\fR Creation of a logfile, per default \fB/var/log/²DPROG².log\fR.
.LP
\fB4)\fR If necessary, creation and making accessible of the directories for DICOM source, archive, target and second target files.
.LP
\fB5)\fR If necessary, creation of the configuration file \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory where the program is located (default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/\fR).
.LP
\fB6)\fR Insertion of a line for the periodic automatic program call in root's crontab (if configured).
.LP
\fB7)\fR If necessary, insertion of sections for the directories mentioned under 4) in /etc/samba/smb.conf; if necessary, insertion of the program user as a samba user.
.LP
\fB8)\fR If necessary, creation of the database (\fBfotosinp\fR) and the table \fBdictab\fR in MariaDB; if necessary insertion of a MariaDB user.
.LP
\fB9)\fR Installation or compilation of \fBdcmtk\fR if not present or too old.
.SH UNINSTALLING
Change in a terminal to the installation directory (for the same installed user, it's \fBcd ~/²DPROG²\fR, otherwise it will be displayed by \fB²DPROG² -info\fR).
.br
Call \fBmake uninstall\fR.
.br
Then the installed \fB²DPROG²\fR will be deleted and the script \fBuninstallinv\fR will be executed in reverse order which has been generated during the installation and execution of ²DPROG².
.br
Thereby additionally installed program packets, permissions, samba shares and firewall exceptions are deleted.
.br
Configuration files, accumulated data and system relevant programs will not be deleted.
.br
Error messages originate mostly in efforts to delete a program already missing and can then be ignored.
.SH RETURN CODES
\fB0\fR: Normal return code
.br
\fB7\fR: The info screen (\fB²DPROG² -info\fR) has been displayed
.br
\fB8\fR: The help has been displayed
.br
\fB10\fR: Initializing of the database failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB11\fR: Checking of the database table \fBdictab\fR failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB98\fR: Program stopped because it is already running once
.br
\fB99\fR: A search command at a link failed
.br
\fB113\fR: An sql command for the mariadb database failed with a miscellaneous error
.br
\fB115\fR: A database entry failed because of a full disk
.br
After calling \fB²DPROG² -vi\fR or \fB²DPROG² -vs\fR the return code of \fBvi\fR/\fBvim\fR will be passed
